docs.abstract: Displays of the flag have become essential to the league, but a push for patriotism has not come without controversy.
docs.snippet: Displays of the flag have become essential to the league, but a push for patriotism has not come without controversy.
docs.lead_paragraph: At noon in the parking lot outside a Carolina Panthers game in November, Dean Nass, 64, pressed a button on his laptop. “The Star Spangled Banner” began to play. His friends and family — 15 in all — put down their barbecued chicken, potato salad and cans of beer and stood at attention.

headline.main: The N.F.L. Wears Patriotism on Its Sleeve. And Its Head. And Its Feet.

docs.abstract: In this lesson students will look at immigrant entrepreneurship and consider different ideas of success between generations.
docs.snippet: In this lesson students will look at immigrant entrepreneurship and consider different ideas of success between generations.
docs.lead_paragraph: In “Chinese Restaurants Are Closing. That’s a Good Thing, the Owners Say.” Amelia Nierenberg and Quoctrung Bui look at the connection between the decline in Chinese restaurants across America and the economic mobility of the second generation. In this lesson, you will consider businesses that make up your own community and ideas of success among different generations and families.

headline.main: Lesson of the Day: ‘Chinese Restaurants Are Closing. That’s a Good Thing, the Owners Say.’

docs.abstract: Food deliverers in New York City are facing a crime wave: Since September, at least 24 e-bikes have been reported stolen.
docs.snippet: Food deliverers in New York City are facing a crime wave: Since September, at least 24 e-bikes have been reported stolen.
docs.lead_paragraph: Food delivery workers in New York City have long been preyed upon by muggers, but with the advent of app-based ordering, many thought they would be less of a target because they usually don’t carry as much cash.

headline.main: They Once Were Attacked for Their Cash. Now It’s Their E-Bikes.
headline.print_headline: Electric Bike Thefts Threaten Livelihoods, and the Lives, of Food Deliverers

docs.abstract: Mr. Roe joins the exodus of Republican lawmakers opting out of re-election before another tough campaign cycle.
docs.snippet: Mr. Roe joins the exodus of Republican lawmakers opting out of re-election before another tough campaign cycle.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON —  Representative Phil Roe, Republican of Tennessee, announced on Friday that he would not seek a seventh term in 2020, becoming the first lawmaker this year to join the exodus of Republican lawmakers opting not to run for re-election as their party eyes another tough campaign cycle.

headline.main: Phil Roe, Tennessee Republican, Announces Retirement From Congress
headline.print_headline: Republican Is the 26th To Step Down In Congress

docs.abstract: He played with leading jazz musicians. He bantered with Merv Griffin. But his best-known work may have been on a children’s cartoon series.
docs.snippet: He played with leading jazz musicians. He bantered with Merv Griffin. But his best-known work may have been on a children’s cartoon series.
docs.lead_paragraph: Jack Sheldon, an accomplished jazz trumpeter who also had a successful parallel career as an actor — but whose most widely heard work may have been as a vocalist on the animated television series “Schoolhouse Rock!” — died on Dec. 27. He was 88.

headline.main: Jack Sheldon, Trumpeter and ‘Schoolhouse Rock!’ Singer, Is Dead at 88
headline.print_headline: Jack Sheldon, 88, Big Band Trumpeter And ‘Schoolhouse Rock!’ Singer, Is Dead
